\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 21. B. repanda} (Willd.) DC.,{\i  Reg. Veg. Syst. Nat.}{\b  2}: 598 (1821) ({\i Diplotaxis saxatilis} DC.). Laxly to densely caespitose perennial; stems up to 50 cm, usually leafless, glabrous or hairy. Basal leaves 1-15 cm, entire to pinnatipartite. Raceme 2- to 45-flowered. Petals 7-30 mm, yellow. Siliqua 10-80 × 1-4·5 mm, variable in shape and proportions, gradually or abruptly attenuate into a seedless beak. Seeds ellipsoidal. 2n = 20.{\i  Usually in rocky or stony places. S.W. Europe.} Ga Hs It.
